*** Tested with gcc 3.2.2 ***
If you need to install the MySQL server execute scripts/installMySQL.sh
execute "make config" 
        --> creates the configuration files
execute "make"
        --> builds libraries and binaries and configures the database
execute the mysql command as suggested by the output of the previous step
        --> creates the DB users and tables
execute "source bossenv.csh" or ". bossenv.sh" 
        --> sets the environment
execute "cd sched_examples; ./registerForkScheduler" 
        --> register the "fork" scheduler


